Fairport Football
June 29 at 3:49 PM Â·

Middle school football "skills training" sessions will begin on Monday, July 6 from 5 pm - 6:30 pm at Greig Field.

Middle school skills sessions are every Monday and Wednesday from 5 pm - 6:30 pm throughout July. All students entering 7th or 8th grade interested in playing football should attend.

All participants must bring shoes, cleats, and a filled water bottle.

Please email cruff@fhevs.org for any questions or concerns. We're looking forward to seeing you there!

Go Skippers!

Middle school skills sessions are every Monday and Wednesday from 5 pm - 6:30 pm throughout July. All students entering 7th or 8th grade interested in playing football should attend.

All participants must bring shoes, cleats, and a filled water bottle.

Kick off #NationalParkWeek with National Junior Ranger Day! The Junior Ranger Program is a great way to explore national parks. You can learn about nature sounds, night skies, or even the Transcontinental Railroad! You'll also learn why national parks matter and how you can be a part of the team that helps keep parks healthy.

We don't care what age you areâ€”just "explore, learn, and protect" your national parks online and become an official Junior Ranger! Look for the virtual badges you can print out and post on your refrigerator. Learn more at https://www.nps.gov/kids/junior-ranger-online.htm

#FindYourVirtualPark #JuniorRangerDay

This is a memo to all OHSAA schools.

There is a mandatory no contact period in place for all sports.

It will not be lifted until April 6 at the earliest.

Practices may tentatively resume on April 6.

Scrimmages/contests may resume on April 11.

This may be adjusted and teams/coaches will be notified.

Thank you for staying strong through this challenging time. We love each and every Skipper athlete and will miss them tremendously during this time. We know how much our athletes will miss the game, their coaches and teammates. We hope each and everyone of you stay healthy and safe.

Thank you,
Sandra Knight

Good luck to the MS girls basketball players, competing today in their final game of the season. 8th graders travel to Geneva to face Lakeside and 7th graders travel to West Geauga MS to face Berkshire. Basketball season is sort of like running a marathon. Our season started with open gyms in October. Practices in November and December, and games in January, February and the first week of March. That is about 5 months of dedication and committment! We are very proud of the effort you put in each day!! Many of you came to play this year and tried something for the first time ever. That's hard to do. Now keep on working - the off-season starts today. ğŸ€âš“ #futureladyskippers #smallbutmighty

post_text:
8th grade students traveled to Canton, Ohio today.

The first stop was the Pro Football Hall of Fame, where students learned more about Gale Sayers and Brian Piccolo, the first NFL teammates to also room together during a time of segregation.

The next stop was at the Ida Saxton McKinley Home and First Ladies National Historic Site.

Our students had a great time exploring many exhibits at both locations and learning about the first ladies who have lived in the White House. Ida Saxton, wife of our 25th President William McKinley was a trailblazer. She worked at her father's business and grew up in Canton, Ohio.

Students selected either a First Lady or Pro Football Hall of Famer to learn more about this month. #LearnPLinAction #Navigators #8thGradeRocks #PersonalizedLearning
